md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-92754ad0" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-e3e1f9ab"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6db6e3e1">Skip To & Read:</span></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-59139275"><i class="sc-pjGMk jrwOpx pf-4674c2e7 fa fa-angle-right" data-pf-type="Icon"></i><a data-color="inherit" data-to-section="pf-fb1d5b1f" href="#"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-c2e75913">What is Black Friday?</span></a></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-bef37b4c"><i class="sc-pjGMk jrwOpx pf-ec5654f3 fa fa-angle-right" data-pf-type="Icon"></i><a data-color="inherit" data-to-section="pf-cc178013" href="#"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-54f3bef3">What is the problem with Black Friday?</span></a></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-867eec56"><i class="sc-pjGMk jrwOpx pf-f9ab4768 fa fa-angle-right" data-pf-type="Icon"></i><a data-color="inherit" data-to-section="pf-c061b280" href="#"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4768867e">What is Arms of Andes doing for Black Friday?</span></a></h3></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-fb1d5b1f" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-2de292ba pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-a99141fb" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-0209a991"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-642de292"><span style="font-weight: bold;">It’s Thanksgiving! </span>For many in the USA, this means the start of the holiday season, family time, lots of delicious food, and the best time to get start on Christmas shopping.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-c7360abc" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-bf08c736 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-6faebf08" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-ded1bde7"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-644516cf">What Is Black Friday?&nbsp;</span></h2><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-bde704d9"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-08c7757c">Thanksgiving and the few days after it – particularly Black Friday and Cyber Monday – mark the start of Christmas shopping, and are some of the busiest shopping days of the year. Black Friday and Cyber Monday seem to be great ways to save money on those holiday “essentials” and gifts, as well as give people the opportunity to upgrade their electronics, wardrobes, and toys for their kids. Many think they are especially useful for low income families, who otherwise might not be able to afford things thought of as essentials (including clothing, cell phones and laptops for example), and even a few luxuries.<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-04d96fae"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-0b58ded1">But as you might expect, if you’re of a more cynical disposition, Black Friday is in no way designed to help <i>less </i>fortunate consumers, but rather <b>help along mass consumerism culture</b>! By putting a time limit on seemingly super good deals, they encourage people to spontaneously buy things they never thought they wanted and generally buy far more than they actually need. Plus, once they get customers in the store (be it a bricks and mortar store or online) with the lure of a ridiculously cheap big-screen TV for example, retailers know that customers will most likely come out with far more than just that!<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-cc178013" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-34e57571 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-93d15ab7" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-0d5ca2e7"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4093d15a">What's The Problem With Black Friday?</span></h2></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-f234e575" data-pf-type="Column"><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-03d4b7b0" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-656931f2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-c4b7a1df">&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Black Friday encourages rampant consumerism</span><span style="font-weight: 700;"><br></span>Even though you might start with a specific purchase in mind, it is almost guaranteed you’ll come out with more than you thought you wanted or needed. You might even end up “upgrading” items like clothing and electronics, because of the "great deals", even though the ones you have don’t need upgrading.<br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-d37eb30b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a1dfa5f2"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Black Friday creates more waste</span><span style="font-weight: 700;"><br></span>Packaging waste is a problem for all commercial enterprises these days, but Black Friday/Cyber Monday are particularly impactful when it comes to increased waste. Tying into the first point, people buy more than they need or want, which automatically comes with more packaging. On top of this, they are more likely to throw away items that are in good working order, as they were able to buy better ones for “such great prices”.<br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-ab2503d4"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a5f234e5"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Black Friday creates more greenhouse gases<br></span>Black Friday and Cyber Monday deals often come with expedited shipping, which actually increases a product/purchase’s carbon footprint, as shipping systems become less efficient and more vehicles have to be on the road at one time in order to fulfil the many orders in diverse locations.<br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-296b3a3a"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-1b85296b"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Covid-19 specific concerns
</span><br>Specific to this year, most countries in the world have spent most of 2020 trying to contain a pandemic of a disease that, while it has little effect on many people, has proven to be deadly for some. That means that the crowds in retail stores on Black Friday, may give extra impulse to the second wave of infections, that is currently happening in the US and in many other countries, especially across Europe.&nbsp;<br></span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-71f41bfc" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-7571f41b pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-e57571f4" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" data-srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-f7f10f89--Black-friday-sale-sign-in-store-window.jpg?v=1606348100 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-f7f10f89--Black-friday-sale-sign-in-store-window_800x359.jpg?v=1606348100&resized 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-f7f10f89--Black-friday-sale-sign-in-store-window_400x180.jpg?v=1606348100&resized 400w" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" alt="black and yellow black friday sale sign in a store window" title="Sale signs will be all over store fronts on Black Friday" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-801356b8 pf-img-lazy" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-c061b280" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-95760302 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-a05b23c0" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-24a05c96"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-92ba9e95">What Does Black Friday Mean For Arms of Andes?</span></h2><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-73d3a05b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-9e957603">The other thing about Black Friday and Cyber Monday, is that they really highlight the mark ups that many companies put on their goods. If a company can sell lots of items at 50 to 70% of their normal retail prices, without taking a real hit, that just shows how much it actually costs to make or procure the goods they are selling. On the other hand, <span style="font-weight: bold;">at Arms of Andes, most of the price of our products is made up of the costs of raw materials, manufacturing, and shipping</span>. <span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Currently, we spend almost no money on marketing, relying on organic search and word of mouth.</span> So what you pay for your clothes is pretty much as close to the base cost as it can be: if we slashed our prices like other online retailers, we wouldn’t last until Christmas!<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-8a49c682"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6c8b8a49">However, <span style="font-weight: bold;">to help welcome you to join our journey and get to know our brand</span>,<span style="font-weight: bold;"> we’re offering a 5% discount</span> on all purchases during Friday, November 27th, which will be applied automatically to your shopping cart.  <span style="font-weight: bold;">We have also decided to offer free shipping</span> on all orders in the US for the foreseeable future, and that starts on Friday too!<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><d